getMyRequests

public java.lang.String getMyRequests(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest aRequest,
                                      int aUserId,
                                      java.util.ArrayList<BusinessArea> aBAList,
                                      WebConfig aConfig,
                                      java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> aRoles,
                                      boolean aIsPrimary,
                                      java.util.TimeZone aPrefZone,
                                      int aFlags)
                               throws java.io.IOException,
                                      java.io.FileNotFoundException,
                                      DatabaseException
This method prepares the query for obtaining the My Requests of a user for the given BA list , HTML serializes these results and returns them.

Parameters:
aRequest - Http Request object to access session.
aUserId - Id of the user.
aBAList - List of BAs from where the user want the MyRequests to be retrieved.
aConfig - User configuration object.
aRoles - Role filter.
aIsPrimary - True if only primary assignee filter is selected and not assignee filter.
aPrefZone - Zone where the user is present.
aFlags - Flags used during rendering.
Returns:
My Requests rendered as HTML.
Throws:
java.io.IOException
java.io.FileNotFoundException
DatabaseException
